The shell version:                            
                                                 
  1. Shell parses the command                        
  2. Forks for echo
  3. Creates a pipe                                  
  4. echo writes to pipe
  5. Forks for socat
  6. socat reads from pipe
  7. socat opens socket, connects, writes
  8. Two processes exit, shell reaps both

  Your C version:

  1. Opens socket, connects, writes, exits

  One process, 3 syscalls, no pipes, no forks, no
  parsing.
